http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#someValues.name: someValuesFrom
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#someValues.description: The property that determines the class that an existential property restriction refers to.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalent.name: equivalentProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalent.description: The property that determines that two given properties are equivalent.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#maxCardina.name: maxCardinality
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#maxCardina.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a maximum cardinality restriction.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#intersecti.name: intersectionOf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#intersecti.description: The property that determines the collection of classes or data ranges that build an intersection.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#members.name: members
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#members.description: The property that determines the collection of members in either a owl:AllDifferent, owl:AllDisjointClasses or owl:AllDisjointProperties axiom.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#propertyDi.name: propertyDisjointWith
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#propertyDi.description: The property that determines that two given properties are disjoint.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#withRestri.name: withRestrictions
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#withRestri.description: The property that determines the collection of facet-value pairs that define a datatype restriction.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#hasValue.name: hasValue
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#hasValue.description: The property that determines the individual that a has-value restriction refers to.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf.name: inverseOf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf.description: The property that determines that two given properties are inverse.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#differentF.name: differentFrom
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#differentF.description: The property that determines that two given individuals are different.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onClass.name: onClass
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onClass.description: The property that determines the class that a qualified object cardinality restriction refers to.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#hasKey.name: hasKey
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#hasKey.description: The property that determines the collection of properties that jointly build a key.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalent.name: equivalentClass
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalent.description: The property that determines that two given classes are equivalent, and that is used to specify datatype definitions.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#allValuesF.name: allValuesFrom
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#allValuesF.description: The property that determines the class that a universal property restriction refers to.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#minQualifi.name: minQualifiedCardinality
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#minQualifi.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a minimum qualified cardinality restriction.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onDatatype.name: onDatatype
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onDatatype.description: The property that determines the datatype that a datatype restriction refers to.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#complement.name: complementOf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#complement.description: The property that determines that a given class is the complement of another class.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty.name: onProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty.description: The property that determines the property that a property restriction refers to.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperti.name: onProperties
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperti.description: The property that determines the n-tuple of properties that a property restriction on an n-ary data range refers to.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#maxQualifi.name: maxQualifiedCardinality
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#maxQualifi.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a maximum qualified cardinality restriction.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#distinctMe.name: distinctMembers
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#distinctMe.description: The property that determines the collection of pairwise different individuals in a owl:AllDifferent axiom.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedT.name: annotatedTarget
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedT.description: The property that determines the object of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#minCardina.name: minCardinality
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#minCardina.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a minimum cardinality restriction.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#oneOf.name: oneOf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#oneOf.description: The property that determines the collection of individuals or data values that build an enumeration.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#datatypeCo.name: datatypeComplementOf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#datatypeCo.description: The property that determines that a given data range is the complement of another data range with respect to the data domain.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedS.name: annotatedSource
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedS.description: The property that determines the subject of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#targetValu.name: targetValue
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#targetValu.description: The property that determines the value of a negative data property assertion.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onDataRang.name: onDataRange
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onDataRang.description: The property that determines the data range that a qualified data cardinality restriction refers to.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWi.name: disjointWith
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWi.description: The property that determines that two given classes are disjoint.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedP.name: annotatedProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedP.description: The property that determines the predicate of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#targetIndi.name: targetIndividual
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#targetIndi.description: The property that determines the object of a negative object property assertion.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#sourceIndi.name: sourceIndividual
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#sourceIndi.description: The property that determines the subject of a negative property assertion.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#unionOf.name: unionOf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#unionOf.description: The property that determines the collection of classes or data ranges that build a union.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#sameAs.name: sameAs
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#sameAs.description: The property that determines that two given individuals are equal.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#propertyCh.name: propertyChainAxiom
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#propertyCh.description: The property that determines the n-tuple of properties that build a sub property chain of a given property.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#qualifiedC.name: qualifiedCardinality
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#qualifiedC.description: The property that determines the cardinality of an exact qualified cardinality restriction.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#assertionP.name: assertionProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#assertionP.description: The property that determines the predicate of a negative property assertion.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#cardinalit.name: cardinality
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#cardinalit.description: The property that determines the cardinality of an exact cardinality restriction.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointUn.name: disjointUnionOf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointUn.description: The property that determines that a given class is equivalent to the disjoint union of a collection of other classes.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#hasSelf.name: hasSelf
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#hasSelf.description: The property that determines the property that a self restriction refers to.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#priorVersi.name: priorVersion
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#priorVersi.description: The annotation property that indicates the predecessor ontology of a given ontology.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#backwardCo.name: backwardCompatibleWith
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#backwardCo.description: The annotation property that indicates that a given ontology is backward compatible with another ontology.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#deprecated.name: deprecated
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#deprecated.description: The annotation property that indicates that a given entity has been deprecated.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#incompatib.name: incompatibleWith
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#incompatib.description: The annotation property that indicates that a given ontology is incompatible with another ontology.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInf.name: versionInfo
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInf.description: The annotation property that provides version information for an ontology or another OWL construct.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#bottomData.name: bottomDataProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#bottomData.description: The data property that does not relate any individual to any data value.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#topDataPro.name: topDataProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#topDataPro.description: The data property that relates every individual to every data value.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#bottomObje.name: bottomObjectProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#bottomObje.description: The object property that does not relate any two individuals.

http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#topObjectP.name: topObjectProperty
http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#topObjectP.description: The object property that relates every two individuals.
